<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1442,1574]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
This species is included in the key here based on the statement by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nakahara" box="[901,1148,1442,1466]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Nakahara, S. (1997) Annotated list of the Frankliniella species of the world (Thysanoptera: Thripidae). Contributions on Entomology, International, 2, 355 - 389." type="journal article" year="1997">
Nakahara (
<number box="[1024,1085,1442,1466]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1997.0">1997</number>
: 
<number box="[1096,1140,1442,1466]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="359.0">359</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
that 
<taxonomicName box="[1204,1301,1444,1467]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hancornia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis box="[1204,1301,1444,1467]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares with 
<emphasis box="[151,263,1480,1503]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">antennata</emphasis>
Hood from 
<collectingCountry box="[410,461,1479,1502]" name="Peru" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Peru</collectingCountry>
the absence of ocellar setae pair I, whereas this pair of setae is present in all other members of the genus. Unfortunately, 
<taxonomicName box="[580,677,1516,1539]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hancornia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis box="[580,677,1516,1539]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from one damaged female, collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1293,1361,1514,1538]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Brazil</collectingCountry>
at Rio de Janeiro, and the possibility that this is merely an aberrant specimen cannot at present be discounted.
</paragraph>
